page.title: 12A TEYNHAM 11 YEAR OLD'S DAY
page.content: Saturday 13th July started with a typical Saturday morning. I got up at 7.30 a.m. and went downstairs. I picked up my comic, 'Suzy', that is delivered. For breakfast I had a chocolate Penguin and cold milk. I went upstairs, had a wash and cleaned my teeth. I got my dancing shoes and went into Sittingbourne by train. My half hour dancing lesson started at 9 a.m. My dad came into Sittingbourne by train. After my lesson I went to my grandad's house. We went to the Kent County Show where I saw the work done by my school. We went home because I was going to be in the Teynham carnival. When I was ready my sister Denise took me to the float. When the carnival finished I went home and watched the 'Live Aid' pop concert on television. Then I went to bed.
